This paper is about Part-Of-Speech (POS) tagging of code-mixed Indian social media text using a conditional random fields (CRF) based system. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for POS tagging, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category. Additionally, the use of CRF models involves probabilistic graphical models, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also involves optimization techniques for CRF models, which makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category.
